Watching this video made me want to tell everyone my hair story lol 
I had long and very healthy hair back then and I got bored of same color for 22 years (I'm 24 now) so I made my sister cut it (bc of covid we couldn't go to hairdresser) and we dyed it a light brown. ( I have dark dark brown hair)
Then a couple of months later my hair turned into orangey shade after one more dying to same color. After my roots came with darker brown it looked really bad and covid was fine so i was able to go to hairdresser finally. I told hairdresser to fix my hair color and give a bit brightness to the ends. (Its called sombre?) And he bleached my whole head  he said it was the only way to fix it and he even said he was doing me a favor. After bleaching he applied hair polish(?) To make it beige as i wanted. When i was leaving the saloon i had a whole light blonde head. I couldnt say anything at the saloon but a day after, it turned into bleached color again(lemon colour we can say). I called him he told me to come and he applied hair polish again and sent me home. 2 weeks later I called him and told him that I look like 45 year old lady but he said this was what I wanted. :(  after a month I dyed it to ash gray by myself so I could go out for a while. 6 months passed and my hair got longer but my bleached hair was the same color between lemon and tangerine. My hair was damaged so bad and I used so much straightener in those months because I couldn't leave it itself, my natural curls were gone. Naturally, it made it worse. So I went to a different saloon he dyed my roots brown, similar to my original color and he applied some dyes to the rest of the hair and he made it look like the girl had  in this video. Like beige and ashy. He applied keratin botox to repair the damage. (This is very popular here) color was really nice and my hair was so soft but I had a problem. I asked him if he could give me some layers from the front and maybe curtain bangs. And he cut it. After some times I realized there were some hairs from my back were as short as my bangs. He.gave.my.back head.bangs..... whenever I blow dry my hair now my bangs from my back rise up and give my head a terrible look.  I look like I have a second head. After 2 months brown dye he did to my roots turned into orangey brown and blonde hair came out again. I know dyes fades out but my hair that has been cutted extremely short from the back makes me sad. I stopped using straightener, I try to fix with blow dryer. I cant curl my hair because it looks awful. Long story short, take care of your natural hair girls. And i wish all hair dressers were as reliable as this ssaem :(
